com.cloudpos.led

Interface LEDDevice

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Device

    public interface LEDDevice
extends Device
    The LEDDevice interface defines the LED device APIs to be used by the applications.

    The LED device object is obtained from the POSTerminal, its' as follows: 

     LEDDevice lEDDevice =
         (LEDDevice) POSTerminal.getInstance().getDevice("cloudpos.device.led");
    Among them, the "cloudpos.device.led" string is to identify the LED device, defined by the specific implementation.

    Uses the LED device object to control the operation of the LED device.

    An app can request permission to access the device, as shown below: 

     <uses-permission android:name="android.permission.CLOUDPOS_LED" />
    See Also:
    Device

      • startBlink

        void startBlink(long delayTurnOn,
              long delayTurnOff,
              int counts)
                throws DeviceException
        This method causes the LED to begin blinking continuously. Durations are specified for ON time and OFF time. The sequence starts with ON time.
        This method is asynchronous. The device receiving this request MUST be able to successfully respond to cancelBlink() and abort the operation.
        Parameters:
        delayTurnOn - The time in milliseconds that the LED must be ON.
        delayTurnOff - The time in milliseconds that the LED must be OFF.
        counts - The number of times the LED is required to blink.
        Throws:
        DeviceException - for the standard reasons that are documented in DeviceException.
